# Onboarding selectable items

See also **`.cursor/rules/app-stroke-1px.mdc`** — all UI strokes are **1px** app-wide.

Use **`onboardingSelectableCard(theme, selected, isLight)`** from `onboardingUi.ts` for every tappable row or choice button in onboarding (goal list, notification toggles row chrome, income type pills, goal-setup focus card, etc.).

## Light mode (default)

- **Border:** `ONBOARDING_SELECTABLE_BORDER_WIDTH` (**1px**) for both selected and unselected — never 2px on these rows
- **Selected:** white background (`surfaceSelected` = `#FFFFFF`), **1px accent border** — no purple fill, **no box-shadow / glow**
- **Unselected:** white background, **1px** neutral `surfaceBorder`
- Selection is communicated by **border + text weight/color only**, not tint or shadow

## Do not

- `boxShadow` or colored glow on selected onboarding options in light mode
- `rgba(62, 55, 255, 0.08)` (or similar) fill on selected rows — keep background white
- One-off `AUTH_THEME` / inline selected styles — use `useOnboardingChrome()` + `onboardingSelectableCard`

## Dark onboarding (legacy)

If `isLight` is false, tinted `surfaceSelected` and subtle shadow may remain — light path must stay flat white + border.
